@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<style>
    body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333;
        margin: 20px;
        background-color: #e9f0f5;
    }

    h2 {
        color: #333;
        font-size: 28px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        text-align: center;
        text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .policy-section {
        background-color: #fff;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
    }

        .policy-section:hover {
            background-color: ##f9f9f9;
        }

    h3 {
        color: #555;
        font-size: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
        padding-bottom: 10px;
    }

    p {
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        line-height: 1.8;
    }

    strong {
        font-weight: bold;
    }
</style>

<h2>@ViewData["Title"]</h2>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h3>1. Information Collection</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Personal Information:</strong> Describe the types of personal data you collect (e.g., name, address, email) and how you collect it (e.g., directly from users, through cookies).
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Usage Information:</strong> Explain what non-personal information you collect automatically (e.g., IP address, browser type) and why (e.g., to improve website functionality).
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Financial Information:</strong> Clarify how financial information (e.g., credit card details) is handled, emphasizing security measures and third-party involvement (e.g., payment processors).
    </p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h3>2. Use of Information</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Purpose:</strong> State the primary reasons for collecting user data (e.g., order processing, customer support) and how it benefits users.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Communication:</strong> Outline how you use collected information to communicate with users (e.g., updates, promotional offers) and provide opt-out options.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Improvement:</strong> Detail how collected data helps improve services and user experience (e.g., analytics, personalization).
    </p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h3>3. Information Sharing and Security</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Sharing Practices:</strong> Explain under what circumstances you share personal information with third parties (e.g., service providers, legal requirements) and how you ensure confidentiality.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Security Measures:</strong> Describe the security protocols in place to protect user data from unauthorized access, breaches, and misuse (e.g., encryption, access controls).
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>User Control:</strong> Inform users about their rights regarding their personal data (e.g., access, correction, deletion) and how they can exercise these rights.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="policy-section">
    <h3>4. Policy Updates and Contact Information</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Policy Updates:</strong> Explain how and when updates to the privacy policy will be communicated to users and where they can access the latest version.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Contact Information:</strong> Provide contact details for users to reach out with questions, concerns, or requests related to their privacy and data handling.
    </p>
</div>
